President Donald Trump has announced his intention to nominate Robert Wallace of Wyoming as an Assistant Secretary for Fish and Wildlife at the Department of the Interior. Wallace, a native of Evanston, Wyoming, is a graduate of the University of Texas at Austin. He has previous government experience as a seasonal ranger and as assistant director of Legislative and Congressional Affairs for the National Park Service. Wallace has also served as chief of staff to United States Senator Malcolm Wallop, chief of staff to Wyoming Governor Jim Geringer, and Republican staff director of the Senate Committee on Energy and Natural Resources. He currently resides in Jackson Hole, Wyoming with his wife and two daughters.